      3.  described inline as gml:Point using the pointRep element (if it is required to give the vertices gml:id's), or by reference to other gml:Points using the pointRep element in the by-reference mode (if Points with id's are already available). 
Relative to a right-handed coordinate system the vertex sequence is      
      5
    /  | \
   /  4  \
 3 / -\- 2
  |/     \  | 
 0____1

For cases where the face order is used implicitly, then the faces are defined with the following vertices

0 - 0 1 4
1 - 1 2 5 4
2 - 2 3 5
3 - 3 0 4 5
4 - 0 3 2 1

      </documentation>
		</annotation>
		<complexContent>
